<TITLE> SAFF football championship deferred 6 months </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Oct 8 (bdnews24.com) - The South Asian Football Federation (SAFF) Football Championship has been deferred by six months because of India's professional league and national football championship. The SAFF meeting in Sri Lanka Monday took the decision to hold the SAFF Football Championship in the last week 0f May in 2008 instead of December this year, said a Bangladesh Football Federation (BFF) press release. BFF acting general secretary Manzoor Hossain Malu, who attended the SAFF meeting, said by phone that the championship had been deferred for India's professional and national football leagues, scheduled for November and to maintain the FIFA calendar on the World Cup pre-qualifying round matches. The meeting also decided to hold the team's draw of the meet on February 26, 2008 in Maldives, co-host of the tournament along with Sri Lanka. 
